Scalp micropigmentation (SMP) 

This procedure helps in creating the illusion of fuller hair. It is performed using an electric tattoo device. ✅

It is used to create tiny, layered dots in different hues of black to replicate the look of a shadow on your scalp. 
It helps in creating a natural-looking depth and definition.✨

Scalp micropigmentation can be performed on people with :

1) Alopecia 
2) Thinning hair
3) Male and female pattern baldness

Blackhead extractions in salon can lead to enlarged pores and unsterile equipments can also lead to infections and eventual scarring.

If you have concerns of scarring using exfoliating and sebum regulating products in your skincare routine and getting chemical peels done that will help in unclogging the pores is the safest option.

Ingrown hair is a recurring problem and will need a permanent solution. Waxing and threading can only temporarily solve the issue and at some point ingrown hair can lead to inflammation and infection. The permanent way of addressing ingrown hair is laser hair removal done in clinic.

Another scary practice going on in most salons are propaganding skin lightening or fairness treatments by doing certain procedures with unknown ingredients. This can give rise to permanent and long term skin issues like pigmentation concerns or making the skin extremely sensitive because of the ingredients unknown. Instead, opt for procedures that are safe and give long-term benefits and aim for brighter and an even skintone. Treatments like q switch laser, erbium laser, skin brightening chemical peels, IV Glutathione as a part of the whole treatment routine achieving a brighter and even skin tone

Additional point ⚠️
I will also not prefer waxing or threading for unwanted hair as this is again a temporary solution that can give rise to tanning and darkening of the areas that are being treated with waxing or shaving instead of a permanent solution like laser hair removal.

I am not saying IV Glutathione is useless 🙅🏻‍♀️Of course, glutathione is a very powerful antioxidant that helps in fighting free radical damage thereby, improving the health of the body and thereby the health of the skin ✨

Yes, when IV Glutathione taken at short intervals and frequently will give rise to slightly brighter skintone. But, it is not a magical fairness treatment and the results are extremely short lived.

You will be able to see even brighter skintone only for as long as you keep taking IV Glutathione drips or supplements.
Do not have over expectations on IV Glutathione 👍
